quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
  21,112,"[The Prophet (ﷺ)] has said, ",1:[i.e., their lies and disbelief.]
  23,64,"Until when We seize their affluent ones with punishment,{1} at once they are crying [to Allāh] for help.",1:[In worldly life, before the punishment of the Hereafter.  Although general, the description includes specifically the punishment of the Quraysh by famine.]
  23,65,"Do not cry out today. Indeed, by Us you will not be helped."
  23,66,"My verses had already been recited to you, but you were turning back on your heels."
  24,46,"We have certainly sent down distinct verses. And Allāh guides whom He wills to a straight path."
  24,47,"But they [i.e., the hypocrites] say, "
  24,48,"And when they are called to [the words of] Allāh and His Messenger to judge between them, at once a party of them turns aside [in refusal]."
  25,10,"Blessed is He who, if He willed, could have made for you [something] better than that - gardens beneath which rivers flow - and could make for you palaces."
  25,11,"But they have denied the Hour, and We have prepared for those who deny the Hour a Blaze."
  25,12,"When it [i.e., the Hellfire] sees them from a distant place, they will hear its fury and roaring."